        "# Objective {.unnumbered}\n",
        "\n",
        ":::{.callout-note}\n",
        "- Assignment 1 focused on **building a structured NLP corpus** from SEC filings.\n",
        "- Assignment 2 focuses on **extracting a specific strategic signal** and engineering a dataset that supports **future LLM retrieval workflows**.\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "Your task is to design a pipeline that extracts **Artificial Intelligence investment signals** from Form 10-K filings and transforms them into a **retrieval-ready corpus**.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Business Context {.unnumbered}\n",
        "\n",
        "Technology analysts and investors increasingly rely on narrative disclosures to understand:\n",
        "\n",
        "* firm-level AI capability investment\n",
        "* digital transformation strategy\n",
        "* infrastructure modernization\n",
        "* competitive positioning\n",
        "\n",
        "These signals appear in:\n",
        "\n",
        "* long narrative filings\n",
        "* inconsistent language\n",
        "* dispersed disclosure sections\n",
        "\n",
        "Your task is to **systematically detect and structure AI investment language**.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Data Source {.unnumbered}\n",
        "\n",
        "You must use the [2024 SEC Form 10-K HTML]{.uublue-bold} located [2024 SEC 10-K Filings - HTML](https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1tqqoqDfcOpGKBoRN7PpAtElcmzKcrbGz?usp=sharing)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Defining the AI Investment Signal\n",
        "\n",
        "You must operationalize **AI investment** as an extraction construct.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Requirements\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Define what counts as AI investment evidence.\n",
        "2. Define what does **not** count.\n",
        "3. Provide examples of valid evidence sentences.\n",
        "4. Develop an initial keyword strategy.\n",
        "5.  Identify relevant filing sections:\n",
        "    1.  Item 1 – Business\n",
        "    2.  Item 1A – Risk Factors\n",
        "    3.  Item 7 – MD&A\n",
        "    4.  Item 7A – Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures about Market Risk\n",
        "\n",
        "## Expected Output\n",
        "\n",
        "* conceptual signal definition\n",
        "* inclusion / exclusion examples\n",
        "* keyword table\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Programmatic Extraction Pipeline\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Using the cleaned corpus:\n",
        "  1. Search for AI-related language using regex / keyword logic.\n",
        "  2. Extract candidate text segments.\n",
        "  3. Attach metadata:\n",
        "    1. company identifier\n",
        "    2. filing section\n",
        "    3. keyword trigger\n",
        "    4. raw evidence text\n",
        "2. Store results in structured format.\n",
        "3. Maintain a **recheck dataset** for extraction failures.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Expected Output\n",
        "\n",
        "* extraction pipeline description\n",
        "* dataset summary\n",
        "* sample extracted evidence\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Chunk Engineering and Retrieval Dataset Construction\n",
        "\n",
        "You will transform extracted evidence into a **retrieval-ready corpus**. This stage focuses on **text engineering**, not modeling.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Required Steps\n",
        "\n",
        "1. [Sentence Processing]{.uublue-bold}: Clean and structure raw text.\n",
        "   1. clean extracted text\n",
        "   2. split into sentences\n",
        "   3. remove noise\n",
        "2. [Chunk Construction]{.uublue-bold}: Build retrieval chunks using a rolling window approach.\n",
        "   1. sentence-based windows\n",
        "   2. overlap strategy\n",
        "   3. approximate token control\n",
        "3. [Rolling Window Chunk Construction]{.uublue-bold}\n",
        "   1. sentence-based windows\n",
        "   2. overlap strategy\n",
        "   3. approximate token control\n",
        "4. [Metadata Attachment]{.uublue-bold}: Ensure each chunk is richly annotated for retrieval.\n",
        "   1. company identifier\n",
        "   2. filing section\n",
        "   3. chunk size metrics\n",
        "   4. source tracking fields\n",
        "5. [Dataset Assembly]{.uublue-bold}: Compile chunks into a structured dataset ready for embedding generation and retrieval workflows.\n",
        "   1. Final dataset should resemble:\n",
        "\n",
        "  ```\n",
        "  chunk_id\n",
        "  company\n",
        "  section\n",
        "  signal_type\n",
        "  chunk_text\n",
        "  sentence_count\n",
        "  approx_token_count\n",
        "  ```\n",
        "\n",
        ":::{.callout-important}\n",
        "You are **not required to generate embeddings in this assignment**. That step will be introduced in Assignment 3.\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "## Expected Output\n",
        "\n",
        "* dataset summary statistics\n",
        "* number of companies represented\n",
        "* number of chunks generated\n",
        "* example chunk inspection\n",
